  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">PROJET TWITEHO AMAGARA</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The purpose of this project  is to provide a service to implement the activities of the TWITEHO AMAGARA Program funded by the European Union and the overall objective of which is to &quot;help mitigate the negative socio-economic impact of the political and security crisis. on the Burundian population by strengthening its resilience capacity and ensuring the continuity and quality of essential basic services. The specific objective of the program is to &quot;contribute to increasing universal accessibility to quality health services at the level of care structures and at the community level, including sexual and reproductive health and meet specific health needs.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Train 42 managers of CDS, hospitals and BDS on essential drugs management modules, the administrative and financial management procedures manual, quality of care management integrating the gender aspect, accountability, complaint management and feedback information to improve beneficiary satisfaction. Train 42 health providers (CDS, BDS, COGES) on the Medical Assistance Card manual. Train 240 community representatives on changing mentalities for sustainable development to reduce barriers around SRH   among other trainings .</narrative>
  </description>
